<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<style>
body, html {
  height: 100%;
  margin-top: 0px;
  margin-right: 0px;
  margin-left: 0px;
  margin-bottom: 0px;
}

.parallax {
  /* The image used */
  background-image: url("https://clarkdc.github.io/images/prism.png");

  /* Full height */
  height: 100%; 

  /* Create the parallax scrolling effect */
  background-attachment: fixed;
  background-position: center;
  background-repeat: no-repeat;
  background-size: 100% 100%;
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<header id="header" class="loading" style="opacity: 0.5;">
  <h1 class="font_0" style="font-size: 66px; line-height: 1.2em;">
	  <span style="font-family:lulo-clean-w01-one-bold,sans-serif; letter-spacing: 0.05em;">
	    [
	    <span class="color_11">ESC</span>
	    ]
	  </span>
  </h1>
</header>

<div class="parallax"></div>

<div style="height:1000px;background-color:white;font-size:36px">
Scroll Up and Down this page to see the parallax scrolling effect.
This div is just here to enable scrolling.
Tip: Try to remove the background-attachment property to remove the scrolling effect.
</div>

<div class="parallax"></div>

</body>
</html>

